"title": "7236: Israel, as united kingdom",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7236",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The 12 tribes proclaimed Saul as their first king in 1050 B.C., and remained united under David and Solomon, until the rebellion of the ten northern tribes in 930 B.C.</p>\n<h2>Israel's request for a king</h2>\n<h3>Israel requested a king because it had been governed by corrupt judges</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:1-1Sam8:5\">1SA 8:1–8:5</a></p>\n<h3>Israel requested a king to be like the other nations</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:19-1Sam8:20\">1SA 8:19–8:20</a></p>\n<h3>Israel requested a king because of the threat from Ammon</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:12\">1SA 12:12</a></p>\n<h3>Israel's request for a king seen as a rejection of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:6-1Sam8:7\">1SA 8:6–8:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:19\">1SA 10:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:16-1Sam12:19\">1SA 12:16–12:19</a></p>\n<h2>Israel under Saul (1050–1010 B.C.)</h2>\n<h3>Israel oppressed by the Philistines</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:19-1Sam13:20\">1SA 13:19–13:20</a></p>\n<h3>Saul chosen as Israel's deliverer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:1\">1SA 10:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:17-1Sam10:25\">1SA 10:17–10:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:14-1Sam11:15\">1SA 11:14–11:15</a></p>\n<h3>Israel victorious under Saul</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:47-1Sam14:48\">1SA 14:47–14:48</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:11-1Sam11:13\">1SA 11:11–11:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:7-1Sam15:8\">1SA 15:7–15:8</a></p>\n<h3>Israel's war with the Philistines</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:52\">1SA 14:52</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:5-1Sam13:7\">1SA 13:5–13:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:20-1Sam14:23\">1SA 14:20–14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:51-1Sam17:53\">1SA 17:51–17:53</a></p>\n<h3>The popularity of David in Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:30\">1SA 18:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:6-1Sam18:9\">1SA 18:6–18:9</a></p>\n<h3>Israel defeated by the Philistines, and the death of Saul</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam31:1-1Sam31:10\">1SA 31:1–31:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr10:1-1Chr10:10\">1CH 10:1–10:10</a></p>\n<h2>Israel under David (1010–970 B.C.)</h2>\n<h3>Civil war in Israel between David and Ish-Bosheth, Saul's son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:1\">2SA 3:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:8-2Sam2:17\">2SA 2:8–2:17</a></p>\n<h3>David appointed king over Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:1-2Sam5:3\">2SA 5:1–5:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:1-1Chr11:3\">1CH 11:1–11:3</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:1\">1SA 16:1</a></p>\n<h3>David makes Jerusalem the capital of Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:6-2Sam5:10\">2SA 5:6–5:10</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:4-1Chr11:9\">1CH 11:4–11:9</a></p>\n<h3>Israel victorious under David</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:1-2Sam8:14\">2SA 8:1–8:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr18:1-1Chr18:13\">1CH 18:1–18:13</a></p>\n<h3>Officials in Israel under David</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:15-2Sam8:18\">2SA 8:15–8:18</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr18:14-1Chr18:17\">1CH 18:14–18:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam20:23-2Sam20:26\">2SA 20:23–20:26</a></p>\n<h3>Civil war in Israel between David and his son Absalom</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:10-2Sam15:12\">2SA 15:10–15:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:1-2Sam18:8\">2SA 18:1–18:8</a></p>\n<h3>God's judgment on Israel during David's reign</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam21:1\">2SA 21:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:1-2Sam24:16\">2SA 24:1–24:16</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:1-1Chr21:15\">1CH 21:1–21:15</a></p>\n<h3>All Israel contributes in preparation for the building of the temple</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:6-1Chr29:9\">1CH 29:6–29:9</a></p>\n<h2>Israel under Solomon (970–930 B.C.)</h2>\n<h3>Officials in Israel under Solomon</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:1-1Kgs4:19\">1KI 4:1–4:19</a></p>\n<h3>Prosperity of Israel under Solomon</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:27\">1KI 10:27</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr1:15\">2CH 1:15</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:20-1Kgs4:25\">1KI 4:20–4:25</a></p>\n<h3>Israel's trade relations under Solomon</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:22\">1KI 10:22</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:21\">2CH 9:21</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:8-1Kgs5:12\">1KI 5:8–5:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:11-2Chr2:16\">2CH 2:11–2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:11-1Kgs10:12\">1KI 10:11–10:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:10-2Chr9:11\">2CH 9:10–9:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:28-1Kgs10:29\">1KI 10:28–10:29</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:28\">2CH 9:28</a></p>\n<h3>Solomon's building programme in Israel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:1-1Kgs6:37\">1KI 6:1–6:37</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr3:1-2Chr3:14\">2CH 3:1–3:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:1-1Kgs7:12\">1KI 7:1–7:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:17-1Kgs9:19\">1KI 9:17–9:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr8:1-2Chr8:5\">2CH 8:1–8:5</a></p>\n<h3>Solomon puts Israelites to forced labour</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:13-1Kgs5:18\">1KI 5:13–5:18</a></p>\n<h2>Division in Israel (930 B.C.)</h2>\n<h3>Opposition to Solomon</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:14-1Kgs11:26\">1KI 11:14–11:26</a></p>\n<h3>Israel divided because of its apostasy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:29-1Kgs11:33\">1KI 11:29–11:33</a></p>\n<h3>Rebellion in Israel against forced labour</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:1-1Kgs12:19\">1KI 12:1–12:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:1-2Chr10:19\">2CH 10:1–10:19</a></p>",
